Subject: [PATCH] fix(wiring): connect context pipeline to LLM + MCP runtime
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

CRITICAL FIX: Context pipeline was built but not wired to runtime.

llm.py:
- build_request_with_context(): compile context → inject into messages → build request
- process_response_with_context(): LLM output → process_turn + tool result extraction
- extract_from_tool_result now WIRED (was orphaned dead code)

mcp_server.py:
- call_tool now uses ToolGateway (was bypassing policy gate)
- Tool results flow into context pipeline (extract → promote if confident)
- _find_workspace_root() helper for context operations

Fixes: #1 (llm context), #2 (MCP context), #3 (tool_result), #10 (ToolGateway bypass)

364 tests passing.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
